Pedipalps
: Femur tetracarinate; DI carina complete, granular; DE carina restricted to proximal two-thirds of segment, granular (fig. 7C); VI carina discontinuous, comprising two or three granules proximally and four or five granules in distal third; VE carina obsolete, restricted to proximal third of segment (³) or vestigial (
♀
) (fig. 7E); dorsal and external intercarinal surfaces with few scattered granules; internal surface with five or six prominent granules and four additional granules on proximal margin (less developed in 
♀
